  "prompt": "What causes road rage?",
  "response": "Road rage can be caused by a variety of factors, including:\n\n1. Traffic congestion: Being stuck in traffic can lead to feelings of frustration and impatience, increasing the likelihood of road rage.\n\n2. Stress: People who are already stressed or angry may be more prone to road rage.\n\n3. Running late: Drivers who are running late may become more aggressive in their attempts to make up time.\n\n4. Anonymity: The sense of anonymity that comes with driving a vehicle can lead some people to behave more aggressively than they would in other situations.\n\n5. Personal beliefs: Some drivers may believe that they are entitled to drive in a certain way, leading them to become aggressive when other drivers do not conform to their expectations.\n\n6. Environmental factors: Poor weather or road conditions can increase stress levels and contribute to road rage.\n\n7. Mental health issues: Certain mental health issues, such as anger management problems, can increase the likelihood of road rage.\n\n8. Alcohol or drug use: Driving under the influence of alcohol or drugs can impair judgement and increase the likelihood of aggressive behavior.\n\nIn general, road rage can be caused by a combination of personal and environmental factors, and can be exacerbated by stress, time pressure, and other external factors.",
